From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AMD <noreply@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 2026 02:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] xilinx-ai-engine: Replace udelay with usleep_range in
 aie_part_maskpoll_register

Replace udelay() with usleep_range() in the aie_part_maskpoll_register
polling loop to avoid CPU busy-waiting. This fixes performance issues
where busy-spinning with udelay() creates contention that prevents UC
DMA operations from completing, which is what the poll is waiting for.

By yielding the CPU with usleep_range(), the UC firmware can complete
its DMA transactions to DDR, allowing the outstanding transaction
counters to clear much faster.

This resolves the slow initialization times observed on columns 1 and 2
during AI Engine partition initialization.

Signed-off-by: AMD <noreply@amd.com>
---
 drivers/misc/xilinx-ai-engine/ai-engine-part.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/xilinx-ai-engine/ai-engine-part.c b/drivers/misc/xilinx-ai-engine/ai-engine-part.c
index 000000000000..111111111111 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/xilinx-ai-engine/ai-engine-part.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/xilinx-ai-engine/ai-engine-part.c
@@ -203,7 +203,7 @@ int aie_part_maskpoll_register(struct aie_partition *apart, u32 offset, u32 dat
 		value = aie_part_ioread32(apart, apart->aperture->base + offset);
 		if ((value & mask) == data)
 			return 0;
-		udelay(usleep_time);
+		usleep_range(usleep_time, usleep_time + 5);
 	}

 	value = aie_part_ioread32(apart, apart->aperture->base + offset);
